## Curriculum-based staged training — implemented

### What was built

**`sim/curriculum.py`** — full rewrite with:
- `StageDifficulty` dataclass: per-stage env randomization ranges (altitude, speed, roll perturbation, waypoint distance, approach distance, etc.)
- `StageConfig` dataclass: name, active modes, difficulty, success threshold, description
- `STAGES` list — 9 stages in the exact order you specified
- `CurriculumManager` class — auto-advances when rolling success rate ≥ 80% over 100 episodes; state persisted to `models/curriculum_state.json` so training survives restarts

**`envs/fixed_wing_env.py`** — updated:
- Accepts `curriculum_manager=` kwarg; all 4 DummyVecEnv envs share the same manager object (single training thread, no race condition)
- `_reset_training()` now uses per-stage difficulty for all randomization ranges
- `_waypoint_reached` flag tracked in `step()`
- `_episode_success()` — meaningful success condition for each mode (not just "no crash")
- Reports `episode_success`, `curriculum_stage`, `curriculum_advanced` in `info` when episode ends

**`train.py`** — updated:
- `_make_curriculum(cfg)` — creates `CurriculumManager` when `curriculum=true`
- `LiveCallback` reads stage from `env0._curriculum` dynamically, pushes gold `STAGE -> X` events on advancement, logs `status_str()` to console

**`config.txt`** — changed default from `curriculum_phase=mixed` to `curriculum_phase=stabilize` so new runs start from the beginning.

### How it works at runtime

```
[CURRICULUM] Starting at stage 'stabilize'
...100 episodes of STABILIZE-only training...
============================================================
  CURRICULUM ADVANCE #1
  'stabilize'  ->  'cruise'
  Cruise and unusual-attitude recovery.
  Modes: ['STABILIZE', 'RECOVERY']
============================================================
```

Mixed missions are only reached after mastering stabilize → cruise → altitude → heading → waypoint → loiter → approach → landing.
